comment.author: 33147718@N05
comment._content: [http://www.flickr.com/photos/51979177@N02] [http://www.flickr.com/photos/angeljim46] we estimated c 1930 based on the other SS ORUNGAL pics taken by Hood. We're not quite sure but perhaps Hood was travelling on the ORUNGAL between Sydney and Brisbane and that may explain all the other photographs? Interestingly, the vessel was plagued with engine problems for its entire career. On 30 November 1929 while en route from from Brisbane to Sydney ORUNGAL broke down completed and was towed by MUNGANA to Sydney for repairs. I've created a set so that they are easier to view www.flickr.com/photos/anmm_thecommons/sets/72157634468247...
